The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, January 16, 2004 				 High life in steel hub
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Durgapur, Jan. 15: Work on the third phase of the Rs 50-crore Durgapur City Centre began today.																								The foundation stone of the centre, which will house a commercial plaza, a residential complex, a shopping mall and a cineplex, was laid by chief minister Budhhadeb Bhattacharjee two years ago. 																								The promoters of the 370,000-square foot facility said it will be a get-all complex with room for shopping, commerce, entertainment, recreation, health, hospitality, medical amenities and homes. 																								The first phase  the retail and commercial plaza on 75,000 sq ft  is complete and the residential complex is nearing completion, said Sanjay Pandey of Bengal Shristi Infrastructure Development Ltd. Kanakangan, the residential wing of the centre, has high-speed elevators, a swimming pool, a club and hi-tech security. A swank multiplex will be close at hand with restaurants, a cineplex and the entertainment centre, Kalangan, said Pandey.
